WEBVTT

1
00:00:05.130 --> 00:00:08.300
(epic theme playing)

2
00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:16.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

3
00:00:53.303 --> 00:00:55.513
♪

4
00:01:48.900 --> 00:01:51.069
(music fades out)

5
00:01:55.448 --> 00:01:58.868
(tense. solemn music playing)

6
00:02:05.417 --> 00:02:07.085
(footsteps approach)

7
00:02:22.767 --> 00:02:24.769
♪

8
00:02:34.446 --> 00:02:36.156
(inhales)

9
00:02:44.289 --> 00:02:46.291
♪

10
00:02:59.471 --> 00:03:02.641
- (bell tolling)
- (street chatter)

11
00:03:08.980 --> 00:03:11.691
- Only one.
- That's enough. stand back.

12
00:03:11.816 --> 00:03:14.941
- (chatter continues)
- (distant horn blowing)

13
00:03:14.945 --> 00:03:16.988
(bell tolling)

14
00:03:18.657 --> 00:03:20.158
knight: Behold!

15
00:03:20.784 --> 00:03:23.828
The traitor dragon Meleys!

16
00:03:23.954 --> 00:03:28.120
- (crowd clamoring)
- Slain at Rook's Rest

17
00:03:28.124 --> 00:03:29.834
by your king!

18
00:03:32.003 --> 00:03:33.459
To Aegon!

19
00:03:33.463 --> 00:03:36.675
(tense music playing)

20
00:03:39.469 --> 00:03:41.968
(crowd murmuring)

21
00:03:41.972 --> 00:03:45.183
- It can't be...
- They killed a dragon!

22
00:03:45.308 --> 00:03:48.311
Towns person 1: Mark my
words. this is a black omen.

23
00:03:52.649 --> 00:03:54.859
♪

24
00:04:03.827 --> 00:04:05.912
- (bell tolling)
- (horse neighs)

25
00:04:06.037 --> 00:04:08.707
towns person 2: Rhaenyra
will answer this.

26
00:04:09.541 --> 00:04:11.209
'Tis an abomination.

27
00:04:12.377 --> 00:04:14.754
Don't they realize
we won the battle?

28
00:04:15.589 --> 00:04:17.841
Strange victory...

29
00:04:18.550 --> 00:04:20.214
if it was one.

30
00:04:20.218 --> 00:04:22.262
♪

31
00:04:31.062 --> 00:04:32.731
(crowd chattering)

32
00:04:37.444 --> 00:04:39.863
- (horn blowing)
- knight: Behold!

33
00:04:40.906 --> 00:04:43.696
The traitor dragon Meleys!

34
00:04:43.700 --> 00:04:45.531
I thought the dragons was gods.

35
00:04:45.535 --> 00:04:49.076
Knight: Slain at Rook's
Rest by your king!

36
00:04:49.080 --> 00:04:51.750
♪

37
00:04:57.422 --> 00:04:59.090
It's just meat.

38
00:05:00.425 --> 00:05:02.594
♪

39
00:05:15.232 --> 00:05:17.234
(bell tolling)

40
00:05:30.288 --> 00:05:32.999
♪

41
00:05:52.310 --> 00:05:54.312
(solemn music playing)

42
00:06:17.043 --> 00:06:19.045
♪

43
00:06:38.523 --> 00:06:40.734
(music softens)

44
00:07:11.056 --> 00:07:13.058
♪

45
00:07:13.892 --> 00:07:16.061
(quiet chattering)

46
00:07:18.688 --> 00:07:19.773
Is he alive?

47
00:07:19.898 --> 00:07:21.900
His Grace...

48
00:07:22.025 --> 00:07:24.945
remains with us. for the moment.

49
00:07:29.407 --> 00:07:31.743
(music fades out)

50
00:07:32.452 --> 00:07:34.700
(quiet chattering)

51
00:07:34.704 --> 00:07:38.458
- (Aegon breathing heavily)
- (tools clinking)

52
00:07:41.586 --> 00:07:43.922
(pus squelching)

53
00:08:03.275 --> 00:08:05.443
(pus squelching)

54
00:08:07.612 --> 00:08:09.281
(grunting)

55
00:08:17.455 --> 00:08:20.333
(quiet chattering)

56
00:08:21.668 --> 00:08:22.915
Is my son going to die?

57
00:08:22.919 --> 00:08:24.754
I'm afraid I cannot say.

58
00:08:25.005 --> 00:08:28.421
Now. if you'll excuse me. Your Grace.
these next hours are most critical.

59
00:08:28.425 --> 00:08:29.634
Of course.

60
00:08:30.135 --> 00:08:33.305
(solemn music playing)

61
00:08:35.807 --> 00:08:37.976
(quiet chattering)

62
00:08:40.979 --> 00:08:42.355
(bone cracks)

63
00:08:42.689 --> 00:08:44.316
Grand Maester Orwyle:
Easy as you can.

64
00:08:48.528 --> 00:08:50.947
♪

65
00:08:59.497 --> 00:09:01.499
(strained breathing)

66
00:09:04.169 --> 00:09:07.297
Someone will have to
rule in his stead.

67
00:09:19.309 --> 00:09:21.019
(music softens)

68
00:09:21.144 --> 00:09:23.021
(footsteps approach)

69
00:09:28.652 --> 00:09:30.362
(birds chirping)

70
00:09:30.487 --> 00:09:33.152
- What happened?
- We took the castle.

71
00:09:33.156 --> 00:09:35.909
At the cost of some 900 men.

72
00:09:37.577 --> 00:09:39.329
So I've heard.

73
00:09:40.914 --> 00:09:43.583
I left a meager garrison
behind to protect it

74
00:09:43.708 --> 00:09:46.211
and the king's dragon.

75
00:09:46.336 --> 00:09:48.380
Sunfyrewas long in the dying.

76
00:09:48.505 --> 00:09:51.216
The king. Ser Criston.
what befell him?

77
00:09:54.761 --> 00:09:57.430
His Grace fought valiantly.

78
00:09:57.556 --> 00:10:00.225
(Criston polishing sword)

79
00:10:03.562 --> 00:10:04.771
And Aemond?

80
00:10:04.896 --> 00:10:08.066
- (silence)
- (birds chirping)

81
00:10:11.903 --> 00:10:14.072
What was his part in this?

82
00:10:17.742 --> 00:10:19.911
I could not say.

83
00:10:23.373 --> 00:10:27.085
Alfred Broome: Our largest
dragon has been killed.

84
00:10:27.210 --> 00:10:31.590
Criston Cole marches about
the Crownlands unchallenged.

85
00:10:32.048 --> 00:10:35.218
Duskendale and
Rook's Rest are gone.

86
00:10:36.261 --> 00:10:37.884
We still have no ground army

87
00:10:37.888 --> 00:10:40.887
but the one we hope
that Daemon will raise.

88
00:10:40.891 --> 00:10:45.057
He who has left us...
after some marital spat.

89
00:10:45.061 --> 00:10:46.934
(quiet groans)

90
00:10:46.938 --> 00:10:49.274
Do you take issue
with me. Ser Alfred?

91
00:10:51.818 --> 00:10:53.987
My loyalty to you
is proven. my queen.

92
00:10:54.112 --> 00:10:56.235
Your loyalty. perhaps.

93
00:10:56.239 --> 00:10:59.071
but your willingness to give
me deference in a time of war.

94
00:10:59.075 --> 00:11:02.241
I could never doubt
your capability.

95
00:11:02.245 --> 00:11:05.165
or your quickness of mind.

96
00:11:06.291 --> 00:11:08.247
It is merely that
the gentler sex.

97
00:11:08.251 --> 00:11:10.670
heretofore. has
not been much privy

98
00:11:10.795 --> 00:11:13.628
to the strategies of battle.

99
00:11:13.632 --> 00:11:15.592
or their execution.

100
00:11:17.135 --> 00:11:18.925
There has been peace
in our lifetime.

101
00:11:18.929 --> 00:11:21.473
You've seen no more
battles than I have.

102
00:11:31.816 --> 00:11:35.153
(light. tense music playing)

103
00:11:41.201 --> 00:11:43.824
Send to Maidenpool and
to Crackclaw Point.

104
00:11:43.828 --> 00:11:44.992
Let them man their garrisons

105
00:11:44.996 --> 00:11:46.619
and give them stores or weapons

106
00:11:46.623 --> 00:11:48.166
if they find them wanting.

107
00:11:49.167 --> 00:11:50.665
If Cole pursues his campaign.

108
00:11:50.669 --> 00:11:53.960
- our allies must be ready.
- We must answer Rook's Rest.

109
00:11:53.964 --> 00:11:56.295
- and Duskendale.
- Bartimos Celtigar: They are lost already.

110
00:11:56.299 --> 00:11:58.839
But Vhagar is
depleted after such

111
00:11:58.843 --> 00:12:00.011
a hard-fought battle.

112
00:12:00.136 --> 00:12:01.300
Lorent Marbrand:
If Aegon is dead...

113
00:12:01.304 --> 00:12:02.677
Steffon Darklyn: We
will soon know it.

114
00:12:02.681 --> 00:12:04.637
Gormon Massey: 'Twould be
a victory in name only.

115
00:12:04.641 --> 00:12:06.806
They will soon prop up
another in his stead.

116
00:12:06.810 --> 00:12:08.019
Bartimos: The time is ripe.

117
00:12:08.144 --> 00:12:09.384
If we can strike King's Landing

118
00:12:09.479 --> 00:12:10.977
before their dragon
is recovered...

119
00:12:10.981 --> 00:12:12.524
Then I myself must do it.

120
00:12:12.649 --> 00:12:16.190
My queen. you are the crown.
It is out of the question.

121
00:12:16.194 --> 00:12:18.818
What would you have me do?

122
00:12:18.822 --> 00:12:21.032
♪

123
00:12:28.540 --> 00:12:30.542
♪

124
00:12:39.342 --> 00:12:41.428
Baela Targaryen: Jace?

125
00:12:43.722 --> 00:12:45.348
Where are you going?

126
00:12:46.558 --> 00:12:50.850
To Harrenhal. To
treat with Daemon.

127
00:12:50.854 --> 00:12:52.226
Rhaenys is fallen.

128
00:12:52.230 --> 00:12:54.107
He must affirm his
loyalty to my mother

129
00:12:54.232 --> 00:12:56.234
and report his standing.

130
00:12:58.945 --> 00:13:01.239
And you think you
will tame him...

131
00:13:01.364 --> 00:13:02.949
when the queen
herself could not?

132
00:13:03.074 --> 00:13:05.865
My mother gladly sends you away

133
00:13:05.869 --> 00:13:07.700
to scout. to fight.

134
00:13:07.704 --> 00:13:10.790
whilst I'm here being forced
to play the coddled princeling.

135
00:13:10.916 --> 00:13:15.128
- It's humiliating. Baela.
- She only protects you.

136
00:13:15.253 --> 00:13:16.588
You are the succession.

137
00:13:16.713 --> 00:13:20.759
Then I must be seen to act
for her claim and mine.

138
00:13:24.471 --> 00:13:27.140
I can sit still no longer.

139
00:13:29.643 --> 00:13:31.269
I must act.

140
00:13:38.777 --> 00:13:40.278
The Freys.

141
00:13:42.280 --> 00:13:44.612
They control the
crossing at the Twins.

142
00:13:44.616 --> 00:13:47.448
Cregan Stark's graybeards
are marching south.

143
00:13:47.452 --> 00:13:50.785
If his men had a direct
route into the Riverlands.

144
00:13:50.789 --> 00:13:52.916
we would not have to
wait for Daemon to act.

145
00:13:53.625 --> 00:13:56.294
I will treat with The
Freys to secure it.

146
00:13:56.419 --> 00:13:58.129
She will not like it.

147
00:13:58.630 --> 00:14:02.509
Then don't tell her.
Not until I'm away.

148
00:14:11.977 --> 00:14:14.145
(Caraxes calls)

149
00:14:15.689 --> 00:14:18.817
Daemon Targaryen: The hour is
late and my dragon is hungry.

150
00:14:18.942 --> 00:14:22.275
(horses neighing) - You have
no choice but to submit.

151
00:14:22.279 --> 00:14:24.151
Our terms are
simple. Lord Bracken.

152
00:14:24.155 --> 00:14:27.867
Renounce the false
king Aegon as a usurper

153
00:14:27.993 --> 00:14:30.662
and bend the knee to me

154
00:14:30.787 --> 00:14:32.451
or your house burns.

155
00:14:32.455 --> 00:14:35.500
I would sooner be the
Lord of Bones and Cinders

156
00:14:35.625 --> 00:14:39.959
than bend my knee before some
heathen Blackwood cunt...

157
00:14:39.963 --> 00:14:41.548
and his hired dragon.

158
00:14:41.673 --> 00:14:43.174
The Brackens were a
people hatched out

159
00:14:43.300 --> 00:14:45.631
of the deepest of the
Seven Hells. Your Grace.

160
00:14:45.635 --> 00:14:47.174
It would be a kindness
to oblige them

161
00:14:47.178 --> 00:14:49.176
and send them back
whence they came.

162
00:14:49.180 --> 00:14:50.469
Did your brother's head

163
00:14:50.473 --> 00:14:53.018
keep on its way
back to you. Willem?

164
00:14:53.351 --> 00:14:55.228
I heard the maggots got to it.

165
00:14:55.353 --> 00:14:58.356
That is quite the
impression. Lord Bracken.

166
00:14:59.190 --> 00:15:01.401
But alas. not an answer.

167
00:15:02.903 --> 00:15:04.905
(horses grunting)

168
00:15:06.865 --> 00:15:08.867
(horse neighs)

169
00:15:11.077 --> 00:15:13.413
We choose fire.

170
00:15:13.538 --> 00:15:16.708
- (horse neighs)
- (Caraxes grumbling)

171
00:15:23.256 --> 00:15:26.676
I did not think they
would be so eager to die.

172
00:15:27.385 --> 00:15:29.262
They made their choice.

173
00:15:29.554 --> 00:15:32.553
- You should've indulged them.
- I need them alive.

174
00:15:32.557 --> 00:15:35.518
I came here to raise
swords. not corpses.

175
00:15:36.061 --> 00:15:39.227
But now you see what my house
has known for generations.

176
00:15:39.231 --> 00:15:41.233
They are pigheaded.
intransigent...

177
00:15:41.358 --> 00:15:43.902
They would rather
burn than succumb.

178
00:15:47.572 --> 00:15:49.741
Exactly the kind of men I need.

179
00:15:51.743 --> 00:15:53.241
It may yet be possible. I think.

180
00:15:53.245 --> 00:15:55.288
for both of us to
achieve our ends.

181
00:15:55.413 --> 00:15:58.079
We have fought them
for an age and more.

182
00:15:58.083 --> 00:15:59.538
Then perhaps you could try

183
00:15:59.542 --> 00:16:01.920
less fighting and more...

184
00:16:05.715 --> 00:16:07.467
persuading.

185
00:16:08.260 --> 00:16:10.971
They are unyielding in battle.

186
00:16:13.932 --> 00:16:15.934
(wind blowing)

187
00:16:17.727 --> 00:16:20.560
But every man has a weakness.

188
00:16:20.564 --> 00:16:23.066
You take my meaning. then.

189
00:16:26.611 --> 00:16:30.782
There are things the crown
itself must not been seen to do.

190
00:16:32.117 --> 00:16:33.618
Show them your worst.

191
00:16:33.743 --> 00:16:36.075
I am your servant. Your Grace.

192
00:16:36.079 --> 00:16:39.124
(tense music playing)

193
00:16:45.797 --> 00:16:47.799
(music intensifies)

194
00:16:57.142 --> 00:17:00.808
Jeyne Arryn: <i>Over the
centuries. many and more armies</i>

195
00:17:00.812 --> 00:17:04.107
have broken themselves
against my bloody gate.

196
00:17:06.151 --> 00:17:08.316
(music fades out)

197
00:17:08.320 --> 00:17:10.488
Are you listening?

198
00:17:11.281 --> 00:17:12.657
My lady.

199
00:17:13.158 --> 00:17:15.827
The Eyrie itself is impregnable.

200
00:17:17.996 --> 00:17:21.333
Unless. of course. we're
descended upon from the sky.

201
00:17:21.458 --> 00:17:24.123
You promised the Queen
Rhaenyra 15.000 swords...

202
00:17:24.127 --> 00:17:27.380
In return for
protection. A dragon.

203
00:17:28.882 --> 00:17:31.718
Then she has
exceeded your terms.

204
00:17:31.843 --> 00:17:33.011
She sent two.

205
00:17:33.553 --> 00:17:36.056
Both still wet from the egg.

206
00:17:36.181 --> 00:17:37.182
(scoffs)

207
00:17:37.682 --> 00:17:40.227
I have hunting hounds
that are more fearsome.

208
00:17:40.352 --> 00:17:42.687
They are dragons nonetheless.

209
00:17:43.188 --> 00:17:44.477
I do not recall you specifying

210
00:17:44.481 --> 00:17:46.191
the size of the beast
in your request.

211
00:17:46.316 --> 00:17:48.193
Will you goad me. child?

212
00:17:48.693 --> 00:17:51.696
When your bread and shelter
now depend on my pleasure?

213
00:17:53.365 --> 00:17:55.408
The dragons will grow...

214
00:17:56.368 --> 00:17:58.578
- in time.
- I don't have time.

215
00:18:00.330 --> 00:18:02.707
I mislike feeling powerless.

216
00:18:04.042 --> 00:18:05.543
So do I.

217
00:18:12.050 --> 00:18:13.839
This will be your chamber.

218
00:18:13.843 --> 00:18:16.054
I'll expect you at
supper this evening?

219
00:18:19.015 --> 00:18:23.228
My sympathies for the
death of your grandmother.

220
00:18:25.564 --> 00:18:27.732
(wind blowing)

221
00:18:31.403 --> 00:18:34.193
The way they spoke at
my small council today.

222
00:18:34.197 --> 00:18:37.697
Mysaria: Do they hold you responsible
for Rhaenys and her dragon?

223
00:18:37.701 --> 00:18:39.411
I would rather they had.

224
00:18:39.911 --> 00:18:42.622
They speak around me. not to me.

225
00:18:43.290 --> 00:18:44.537
(sighs) They would
make me queen.

226
00:18:44.541 --> 00:18:46.706
but they wish to keep
me here. confined.

227
00:18:46.710 --> 00:18:49.254
They betray their own smallness.

228
00:18:49.796 --> 00:18:51.089
In truth. I cannot fault them.

229
00:18:51.214 --> 00:18:55.381
I am now the sovereign.
I cannot do as I please.

230
00:18:55.385 --> 00:18:58.092
And war has ever
been for men to make.

231
00:18:58.096 --> 00:19:01.596
You are your father's
chosen successor.

232
00:19:01.600 --> 00:19:04.056
He did not prepare me to fight.

233
00:19:04.060 --> 00:19:05.937
If I had been a son.

234
00:19:06.062 --> 00:19:09.608
a sword thrust into my hand
the moment I could walk.

235
00:19:10.108 --> 00:19:12.402
Instead. I was given
my father's cup...

236
00:19:12.944 --> 00:19:15.488
taught the name of
every lord and castle

237
00:19:15.614 --> 00:19:17.069
between Storm's
End and the Twins.

238
00:19:17.073 --> 00:19:20.285
but not the difference
between hilt and foible.

239
00:19:21.161 --> 00:19:22.954
And they know it.

240
00:19:24.289 --> 00:19:27.914
- And Daemon as well...
- Shall your evening meal be served here. Your Grace?

241
00:19:27.918 --> 00:19:29.628
(sharply) Not now.

242
00:19:30.587 --> 00:19:33.798
(distant dragons grumbling)

243
00:19:35.467 --> 00:19:37.177
Will you send to him?

244
00:19:38.595 --> 00:19:41.427
For too long. I have
looked to him for strength.

245
00:19:41.431 --> 00:19:43.516
If I must be supplicant
to my own husband.

246
00:19:43.642 --> 00:19:45.477
what does that make me?

247
00:19:48.813 --> 00:19:52.025
I do not know my part. Mysaria.

248
00:19:54.861 --> 00:19:57.822
The path I walk has
never been trod.

249
00:19:58.823 --> 00:20:02.619
Criston Cole made a mistake.

250
00:20:03.995 --> 00:20:08.287
Parading a dragon's head through
the streets like a prize of war.

251
00:20:08.291 --> 00:20:10.331
but the people see an ill omen.

252
00:20:10.335 --> 00:20:11.832
(scoffs) Yes. as do I.

253
00:20:11.836 --> 00:20:15.169
They are afraid.
bread is scarce.

254
00:20:15.173 --> 00:20:16.629
the king has fallen.

255
00:20:16.633 --> 00:20:19.219
they whisper to each other
that when Viserys lived.

256
00:20:19.344 --> 00:20:21.467
- there was peace.
- (sighs)

257
00:20:21.471 --> 00:20:24.224
But will whispers
tear down stone...

258
00:20:24.349 --> 00:20:25.725
or break shields?

259
00:20:25.850 --> 00:20:29.229
Do not underestimate
your subjects.

260
00:20:29.354 --> 00:20:30.855
They are a thousand-thousand

261
00:20:30.981 --> 00:20:32.645
living in the shadow
of the Red Keep

262
00:20:32.649 --> 00:20:35.193
and forgotten for too long.

263
00:20:35.860 --> 00:20:38.071
And you think they
will turn to me.

264
00:20:38.196 --> 00:20:42.701
To the discontented.
rumors are feed.

265
00:20:43.535 --> 00:20:47.201
(light. tense music playing)

266
00:20:47.205 --> 00:20:48.999
Your Grace.

267
00:20:51.084 --> 00:20:55.714
What you cannot do.
let others do for you.

268
00:20:56.840 --> 00:21:00.172
There is more than one
way to fight a war.

269
00:21:00.176 --> 00:21:02.220
(music intensifies)

270
00:21:13.398 --> 00:21:15.609
♪

271
00:21:20.238 --> 00:21:22.194
(music fades out)

272
00:21:22.198 --> 00:21:24.864
Baela: The thought of
her lying in a field.

273
00:21:24.868 --> 00:21:27.746
broken amongst her enemies.

274
00:21:38.089 --> 00:21:42.302
Did your grandmother ever tell you
of the night she claimed Meleys?

275
00:21:43.303 --> 00:21:45.305
She snuck into the Dragonpit.

276
00:21:45.931 --> 00:21:48.433
She knew that place
better than any Elder.

277
00:21:48.934 --> 00:21:51.102
They say she could
see in the dark.

278
00:21:52.604 --> 00:21:54.439
My father was furious.

279
00:21:54.564 --> 00:21:56.562
His own mother's dragon.

280
00:21:56.566 --> 00:21:57.943
the fastest beast ever known.

281
00:21:58.068 --> 00:21:59.899
- and she'd have none of him.
- (Rhaenyra chuckles)

282
00:21:59.903 --> 00:22:02.405
But bent her neck to Rhaenys.

283
00:22:03.448 --> 00:22:05.617
She was fierce...

284
00:22:06.743 --> 00:22:08.954
in love and in anger.

285
00:22:11.456 --> 00:22:15.168
She did not always
care for me. but...

286
00:22:16.795 --> 00:22:21.007
for what she gave me in
the end. I'm grateful.

287
00:22:26.805 --> 00:22:29.933
I wished I had known
her when she was young.

288
00:22:35.480 --> 00:22:39.818
- (chuckles) You are very like her in some ways.
- (Baela chuckles)

289
00:22:42.320 --> 00:22:47.280
And with her gone... I
must rely on you. I think.

290
00:22:47.284 --> 00:22:49.949
Your Grace? (sniffles)

291
00:22:49.953 --> 00:22:52.706
Would you give this
to your grandsire?

292
00:23:04.134 --> 00:23:06.845
I do not wish to stand alone.

293
00:23:08.346 --> 00:23:10.511
(eerie rumbling)

294
00:23:10.515 --> 00:23:12.309
female voice: Daemon.

295
00:23:17.063 --> 00:23:18.398
<i>Daemon.</i>

296
00:23:19.149 --> 00:23:22.027
<i>You were always the strong one.</i>

297
00:23:23.862 --> 00:23:26.698
The finest swordsman...

298
00:23:29.367 --> 00:23:32.037
the fearless dragon rider.

299
00:23:33.830 --> 00:23:37.584
<i>Your brother had great
love in his heart...</i>

300
00:23:37.709 --> 00:23:39.878
(heavy breathing)

301
00:23:41.755 --> 00:23:44.216
<i>...but he lacked
your constitution.</i>

302
00:23:45.050 --> 00:23:47.844
<i>Viserys was unsuited
for the crown...</i>

303
00:23:50.889 --> 00:23:54.935
<i>but you... Daemon. you
were made to wear it.</i>

304
00:24:03.235 --> 00:24:05.237
(heavy breathing)

305
00:24:15.080 --> 00:24:18.250
<i>If only you'd been born first.</i>

306
00:24:19.459 --> 00:24:21.920
My favorite son.

307
00:24:28.093 --> 00:24:31.471
(echoing) Is the duck not
to your liking. Your Grace?

308
00:24:36.434 --> 00:24:40.063
(normal) There's also
goose. if you'd prefer it.

309
00:24:41.731 --> 00:24:43.604
I like the goose. myself.

310
00:24:43.608 --> 00:24:46.069
(dinnerware clattering)

311
00:24:46.945 --> 00:24:49.281
(Alys pouring wine)

312
00:24:51.825 --> 00:24:53.285
Uh. I'm not hungry.

313
00:24:53.410 --> 00:24:55.620
Simon Strong: I was saying.
given the rather dire news

314
00:24:55.745 --> 00:24:57.581
from Rook's Rest...

315
00:24:58.415 --> 00:25:02.415
it appears the winds have shifted and
each side has suffered great loss.

316
00:25:02.419 --> 00:25:06.006
and will be unsure
of what is to follow.

317
00:25:07.132 --> 00:25:10.089
A good time. then. for
a show of strength.

318
00:25:10.093 --> 00:25:11.257
I believe Willem Blackwood

319
00:25:11.261 --> 00:25:13.930
is bringing House
Bracken to heel.

320
00:25:15.140 --> 00:25:18.518
We must ready the castle
to receive a great host.

321
00:25:20.812 --> 00:25:22.643
You seem sure of this.

322
00:25:22.647 --> 00:25:25.438
All men may be led. Ser Simon.

323
00:25:25.442 --> 00:25:27.193
Even Rivermen.

324
00:25:28.153 --> 00:25:32.157
'Tis a matter of showing them
whom it behooves them to follow.

325
00:25:33.325 --> 00:25:35.660
How does the work here progress?

326
00:25:35.994 --> 00:25:39.785
Oh. um... we're drawing
water for the kitchens

327
00:25:39.789 --> 00:25:42.167
- and lighting the forges.
- Very well.

328
00:25:42.292 --> 00:25:44.790
That is merely the
beginning. of course.

329
00:25:44.794 --> 00:25:46.546
The roof alone
has needed tending

330
00:25:46.671 --> 00:25:47.627
since the reign of Aenys.

331
00:25:47.631 --> 00:25:48.836
And the storerooms.

332
00:25:48.840 --> 00:25:50.884
And...

333
00:25:51.009 --> 00:25:53.511
and the Wailing
Tower. (chuckles)

334
00:25:54.012 --> 00:25:56.514
The bats have made the
corridors almost impassable

335
00:25:56.640 --> 00:25:58.642
with the quantity of their...

336
00:25:59.684 --> 00:26:01.228
Their shit.

337
00:26:03.355 --> 00:26:05.232
I venture there are
smiths and armorers

338
00:26:05.357 --> 00:26:07.813
to be found near
Nutton and Riverbend.

339
00:26:07.817 --> 00:26:09.861
Well. send for them.
and levy the farmers

340
00:26:09.986 --> 00:26:11.988
from Antlers to High Heart.

341
00:26:12.197 --> 00:26:16.034
Task their huntsmen to
bring us meat and wood.

342
00:26:16.159 --> 00:26:18.824
Um. there is. of course.
the matter of payment.

343
00:26:18.828 --> 00:26:20.493
(clattering stops)

344
00:26:20.497 --> 00:26:25.043
After the. the tragedy
that befell his father...

345
00:26:25.377 --> 00:26:31.170
Larys transferred his family's
wealth to King's Landing.

346
00:26:31.174 --> 00:26:33.593
Is there any gold
left in your coffers?

347
00:26:33.718 --> 00:26:38.390
Enough to keep this small
establishment you see fed and warm.

348
00:26:39.391 --> 00:26:40.892
Relatively.

349
00:26:43.270 --> 00:26:46.727
I... I rather thought.
Your Grace. as

350
00:26:46.731 --> 00:26:50.068
emissary to the Queen

351
00:26:50.193 --> 00:26:54.026
that p-perhaps she could
provide the necessary coin

352
00:26:54.030 --> 00:26:57.617
- if you could only write to her.
- No.

353
00:26:57.742 --> 00:26:59.744
Harrenhal is my command.

354
00:27:00.203 --> 00:27:03.081
I shall guarantee
the payment myself.

355
00:27:03.915 --> 00:27:05.709
(mouths) Up. up.

356
00:27:08.753 --> 00:27:10.755
Very well. Your Grace.

357
00:27:11.089 --> 00:27:14.259
You should address
me as "my king."

358
00:27:14.593 --> 00:27:16.261
But you're the prince.

359
00:27:16.595 --> 00:27:18.930
What would you call the
husband of the queen?

360
00:27:19.055 --> 00:27:20.720
- Well. the king...
- Daemon: There it is. then.

361
00:27:20.724 --> 00:27:22.267
...consort.

362
00:27:23.268 --> 00:27:26.229
That last bit seems
unnecessary. don't you think?

363
00:27:28.607 --> 00:27:30.150
(sighing)

364
00:27:31.943 --> 00:27:33.900
Orwyle: The armor
was Valyrian steel.

365
00:27:33.904 --> 00:27:38.283
but His Grace suffered grievous
burns over much of his body.

366
00:27:39.242 --> 00:27:41.119
He has many broken bones.

367
00:27:41.244 --> 00:27:44.619
I fear there are
more injuries within.

368
00:27:44.623 --> 00:27:46.625
injuries we cannot see.

369
00:27:48.126 --> 00:27:50.462
(inhales) We are
grateful for your works.

370
00:27:50.587 --> 00:27:51.588
Grand Maester.

371
00:27:52.672 --> 00:27:55.258
- Has he woken?
- No.

372
00:27:56.509 --> 00:28:01.181
I must admit. I'm not
sure he will ever wake.

373
00:28:01.306 --> 00:28:04.517
I have plied my crafts
to their fullest extents.

374
00:28:04.643 --> 00:28:08.813
Our king's fate lies
with the gods now.

375
00:28:19.324 --> 00:28:22.327
A king cannot rule in his sleep.

376
00:28:22.452 --> 00:28:24.829
The realm will have
noticed his absence.

377
00:28:25.330 --> 00:28:29.042
Let them hear of his great
deeds at Rook's Rest.

378
00:28:29.167 --> 00:28:31.878
But now we must name a
regent to take his place

379
00:28:32.003 --> 00:28:33.672
until he recovers...

380
00:28:36.007 --> 00:28:37.342
or does not.

381
00:28:38.843 --> 00:28:41.133
A wise strategy. Your Grace.

382
00:28:41.137 --> 00:28:42.847
A regency will assure the people

383
00:28:42.973 --> 00:28:45.517
of the stability of the crown.

384
00:28:48.061 --> 00:28:51.189
Did you have a candidate
in mind. Your Grace?

385
00:28:51.648 --> 00:28:53.368
I myself served in this
role for my husband.

386
00:28:53.483 --> 00:28:55.022
I am well-prepared
to do it again.

387
00:28:55.026 --> 00:28:56.482
You played your part admirably

388
00:28:56.486 --> 00:28:58.150
in a time of peace. Your Grace.

389
00:28:58.154 --> 00:29:00.653
but circumstances have changed.

390
00:29:00.657 --> 00:29:02.367
(sarcastically) And
here I had forgotten.

391
00:29:02.492 --> 00:29:04.657
Ironrod: The king does
not lack for heirs.

392
00:29:04.661 --> 00:29:09.704
The obvious choice is his
immediate successor. Prince Aemond.

393
00:29:09.708 --> 00:29:11.038
Tyland Lannister: Agreed.

394
00:29:11.042 --> 00:29:13.874
Aemond is young.

395
00:29:13.878 --> 00:29:16.840
And his lack of restraint
has already cost us dearly.

396
00:29:26.057 --> 00:29:30.228
Orwyle: It is experience that
offers the surest path to security.

397
00:29:30.353 --> 00:29:33.352
Queen Alicent ably shouldered
the duties of the realm

398
00:29:33.356 --> 00:29:35.062
when her husband's
health failed him.

399
00:29:35.066 --> 00:29:36.397
Experience is valuable. yes.

400
00:29:36.401 --> 00:29:37.857
but the dowager
queen is a woman.

401
00:29:37.861 --> 00:29:41.114
I am no stranger to rule or
to sitting at this council.

402
00:29:41.239 --> 00:29:42.528
Aemond is a fearsome
dragon rider.

403
00:29:42.532 --> 00:29:43.863
His skill is best
employed in the field.

404
00:29:43.867 --> 00:29:46.866
but my experience is
needed here. at this table.

405
00:29:46.870 --> 00:29:49.243
No offense was meant.
Your Grace. but...

406
00:29:49.247 --> 00:29:54.419
- at a time when we must show strength.
- Lord Larys?

407
00:29:54.544 --> 00:29:57.213
I agree. Your Grace. It
must be Prince Aemond.

408
00:29:58.924 --> 00:30:01.380
What would it say if. in
response to Rhaenyra's crowning.

409
00:30:01.384 --> 00:30:03.803
we raised up a woman of our own?

410
00:30:06.598 --> 00:30:08.099
But. um...

411
00:30:09.476 --> 00:30:11.390
but the Hand speaks
for the king's voice.

412
00:30:11.394 --> 00:30:13.647
Ser Criston. what say you?

413
00:30:20.445 --> 00:30:22.822
Aemond is the next in line.

414
00:30:24.950 --> 00:30:26.493
It must be him.

415
00:30:30.997 --> 00:30:33.250
Aemond Targaryen:
It's agreed then.

416
00:30:54.479 --> 00:30:56.815
What is our standing
in the Riverlands?

417
00:30:58.316 --> 00:31:00.940
Tyland: Uh. the
banners of House Tully

418
00:31:00.944 --> 00:31:03.150
are in disarray. Your Grace.

419
00:31:03.154 --> 00:31:04.364
Prince Daemon has little hope

420
00:31:04.489 --> 00:31:06.988
of fielding an army
of any size. for now.

421
00:31:06.992 --> 00:31:08.614
(voices fading)

422
00:31:08.618 --> 00:31:10.616
Larys Strong: We would do well to
send word to young Oscar Tully.

423
00:31:10.620 --> 00:31:12.618
- (Alicent breathing heavily)
- It's only a matter of time

424
00:31:12.622 --> 00:31:14.996
before he inherits his
grandsire's mantle.

425
00:31:15.000 --> 00:31:17.002
Aemond: Tell me. Lord Strong.

426
00:31:17.127 --> 00:31:18.545
how I can trust the
counsel of a man

427
00:31:18.670 --> 00:31:20.213
who leaves the jewel
of the Riverlands

428
00:31:20.338 --> 00:31:22.841
to be plucked by our enemy?

429
00:31:26.344 --> 00:31:27.846
Your brother's host
can meet Daemon.

430
00:31:27.971 --> 00:31:29.180
He should quicken its pace

431
00:31:29.306 --> 00:31:30.303
and check the Rivermen

432
00:31:30.307 --> 00:31:31.804
while their banners
are in disarray.

433
00:31:31.808 --> 00:31:34.060
Tyland: I shall send
Lord Jason encouragement.

434
00:31:34.185 --> 00:31:37.022
- Aemond: What else?
- Orwyle: We might turn our attention

435
00:31:37.147 --> 00:31:39.478
to the smallfolk here
in King's Landing.

436
00:31:39.482 --> 00:31:42.027
They have grown weary of
the Sea Snake's blockade.

437
00:31:42.152 --> 00:31:44.195
Aemond: So have we all.

438
00:31:44.321 --> 00:31:45.526
Orwyle: Many are
fleeing the city.

439
00:31:45.530 --> 00:31:48.867
spreading word of
their fear and unrest.

440
00:31:49.200 --> 00:31:52.158
Aemond: Mm. then let
the gates be closed.

441
00:31:52.162 --> 00:31:54.327
♪

442
00:31:54.331 --> 00:31:56.996
No one is to leave or enter.
save with our consent.

443
00:31:57.000 --> 00:31:59.878
Merchants. so forth.

444
00:32:01.713 --> 00:32:04.045
(heavy breathing)

445
00:32:04.049 --> 00:32:06.009
(clearly) Go to your tasks.

446
00:32:06.718 --> 00:32:09.217
We shall meet again
at first light.

447
00:32:09.221 --> 00:32:13.350
Oh. and someone cut down
the fucking ratcatchers.

448
00:32:15.852 --> 00:32:17.103
(coughs)

449
00:32:17.229 --> 00:32:20.106
- (outside street chatter)
- (baby crying)

450
00:32:20.232 --> 00:32:22.567
Kat: The city's
safe no longer.

451
00:32:24.236 --> 00:32:25.737
There is no food.

452
00:32:26.613 --> 00:32:28.694
Our neighbors are
stealing from each other.

453
00:32:28.698 --> 00:32:29.950
We must get out.

454
00:32:30.075 --> 00:32:31.864
And where would you have us go?

455
00:32:31.868 --> 00:32:34.079
North. maybe? South?

456
00:32:34.746 --> 00:32:36.744
For all we know. every road
leads into the dragons' teeth.

457
00:32:36.748 --> 00:32:39.251
Like the one they carted
through the streets?

458
00:32:39.918 --> 00:32:44.297
You think Rhaenyra will let
such an affront go unchallenged?

459
00:32:47.217 --> 00:32:49.928
We should make for Tumbleton.

460
00:32:50.053 --> 00:32:51.972
My brother will have room.

461
00:32:52.097 --> 00:32:53.932
You would have me turn beggar?

462
00:32:55.392 --> 00:32:57.102
(daughter groans)

463
00:32:59.938 --> 00:33:02.728
Are we not beggars already?

464
00:33:02.732 --> 00:33:04.442
Have you been paid
for those machines

465
00:33:04.568 --> 00:33:05.439
you were forced to build?

466
00:33:05.443 --> 00:33:07.153
The king has promised payment.

467
00:33:07.279 --> 00:33:10.282
(hushed) The king has lied!

468
00:33:13.952 --> 00:33:15.120
(coughs)

469
00:33:21.793 --> 00:33:23.628
By all means...

470
00:33:24.296 --> 00:33:27.841
stay and wait for his
empty promises. husband.

471
00:33:29.759 --> 00:33:32.804
With them. you can feed
the mouths of ghosts.

472
00:33:44.316 --> 00:33:46.526
(dog whimpering)

473
00:33:48.987 --> 00:33:50.989
(indistinct chatter)

474
00:33:57.996 --> 00:33:59.664
(body thuds)

475
00:34:12.135 --> 00:34:14.137
Presumed you'd be here.

476
00:34:14.512 --> 00:34:17.182
Seeing faithfully to the
Prince Regent's commands.

477
00:34:17.724 --> 00:34:19.805
Aemond is the next in line.

478
00:34:19.809 --> 00:34:22.975
- It is the order of things.
- You know what he is...

479
00:34:22.979 --> 00:34:25.023
what he has somehow become.

480
00:34:27.692 --> 00:34:29.148
Has your loyalty faded?

481
00:34:29.152 --> 00:34:31.150
Or does it flourish
only at night

482
00:34:31.154 --> 00:34:34.032
and flee the
sunrise like a moth?

483
00:34:37.661 --> 00:34:39.200
What I saw at Rook's Rest...

484
00:34:39.204 --> 00:34:42.666
What? What did you see?

485
00:34:46.544 --> 00:34:48.713
Their armor melted.

486
00:34:50.382 --> 00:34:53.051
There were men walking.
They were on fire.

487
00:34:56.388 --> 00:34:58.723
We have given the
war to the dragons.

488
00:35:00.225 --> 00:35:01.893
A dragon rider should lead us.

489
00:35:06.231 --> 00:35:08.441
And what of justice.
of temperance?

490
00:35:08.567 --> 00:35:11.736
Or is strength now
to be our only god?

491
00:35:17.075 --> 00:35:19.077
So you cast me aside.

492
00:35:20.245 --> 00:35:22.247
Have I not spared you?

493
00:35:23.915 --> 00:35:27.877
What we must do
now is... terrible.

494
00:35:29.588 --> 00:35:31.590
Will you preside over it?

495
00:35:32.090 --> 00:35:36.052
- Is this who you are. Alicent?
- I did not ask to be spared.

496
00:35:39.431 --> 00:35:41.641
And I did not give you
leave to speak my name.

497
00:35:47.439 --> 00:35:49.608
(loud chattering)

498
00:35:54.487 --> 00:35:56.402
gold cloak: Halt!

499
00:35:56.406 --> 00:35:58.658
(crowd shouting)

500
00:36:01.953 --> 00:36:03.121
Stay back!

501
00:36:04.789 --> 00:36:06.750
Towns person: We've
got to get out!

502
00:36:07.417 --> 00:36:08.960
Gold cloak: Somebody get him!

503
00:36:09.628 --> 00:36:11.630
Stay back! No!

504
00:36:11.755 --> 00:36:13.965
Holdfast. hold fast!

505
00:36:14.090 --> 00:36:16.635
- (shouting. fighting)
- Stay back! Hold!

506
00:36:21.306 --> 00:36:22.641
Back!

507
00:36:23.475 --> 00:36:26.603
Disperse. disperse!

508
00:36:27.520 --> 00:36:29.814
By order of Aemond Targaryen.

509
00:36:29.940 --> 00:36:32.692
Prince Regent and
Protector of the Realm...

510
00:36:32.817 --> 00:36:35.107
- Aemond?
- Does he mean the king?

511
00:36:35.111 --> 00:36:37.652
- I don't know.
- You cannot keep us here!

512
00:36:37.656 --> 00:36:40.613
- You are ordered to return to your homes!
- We want meat!

513
00:36:40.617 --> 00:36:42.281
- Meat!
- Meat!

514
00:36:42.285 --> 00:36:44.120
(shouting)

515
00:36:50.335 --> 00:36:52.458
(crowd. gold cloaks clamoring)

516
00:36:52.462 --> 00:36:54.005
gold cloak: Stay back!

517
00:36:56.174 --> 00:36:57.884
(grumbles)

518
00:37:01.680 --> 00:37:06.138
Forrest Frey: Our Lord Grover Tully
has not declared for Rhaenyra.

519
00:37:06.142 --> 00:37:08.474
It means death to bare
steel against your liege.

520
00:37:08.478 --> 00:37:10.855
as I'm sure my prince is aware.

521
00:37:12.357 --> 00:37:14.693
And against your queen?

522
00:37:16.861 --> 00:37:17.862
Hm?

523
00:37:21.366 --> 00:37:25.328
(sighs) Jason Lannister
is marshaling to the west.

524
00:37:26.162 --> 00:37:28.582
We need to check him
before he reaches Riverrun.

525
00:37:29.374 --> 00:37:31.330
That requires passage.

526
00:37:31.334 --> 00:37:33.666
And if Stark's army is too slow?

527
00:37:33.670 --> 00:37:35.501
The wind's rising.

528
00:37:35.505 --> 00:37:37.211
Winter is nigh upon us.

529
00:37:37.215 --> 00:37:38.717
Our hesitance does not lie

530
00:37:38.842 --> 00:37:40.840
in Rhaenyra as Queen.

531
00:37:40.844 --> 00:37:45.219
nor in the ruminations
of Lord Tully. the oaf.

532
00:37:45.223 --> 00:37:48.014
Our fear lies in Vhagar.

533
00:37:48.018 --> 00:37:51.017
You fear a dragon leagues away

534
00:37:51.021 --> 00:37:53.940
when mine own sits
outside your walls?

535
00:37:54.065 --> 00:37:56.067
(wind blowing)

536
00:37:58.028 --> 00:38:01.698
- Do you offer us your protection?
- I do.

537
00:38:07.954 --> 00:38:11.078
And the protection of my uncle.

538
00:38:11.082 --> 00:38:15.462
And Daemon. I'm sure.
has consented to this?

539
00:38:15.587 --> 00:38:17.543
He will do as his
queen commands.

540
00:38:17.547 --> 00:38:19.545
That does lend us some comfort.

541
00:38:19.549 --> 00:38:20.880
Though it occurs
to me that dragons

542
00:38:20.884 --> 00:38:24.387
- cannot be in two places at once.
- Or three.

543
00:38:27.307 --> 00:38:29.226
What do you want?

544
00:38:31.228 --> 00:38:35.144
Larys Strong has been
relieved of his castle.

545
00:38:35.148 --> 00:38:38.652
Does the queen intend
to raise up a new lord?

546
00:38:42.822 --> 00:38:44.407
You want Harrenhal.

547
00:38:55.669 --> 00:38:59.673
(light. tense music playing)

548
00:39:03.134 --> 00:39:08.306
For that... my mother will
want more than your crossing.

549
00:39:09.933 --> 00:39:12.143
What does Her Grace desire?

550
00:39:14.646 --> 00:39:16.982
Bent knees.

551
00:39:18.817 --> 00:39:21.027
(music intensifies)

552
00:39:41.882 --> 00:39:44.217
(music fades out)

553
00:39:44.342 --> 00:39:47.053
(indistinct chatter)

554
00:39:47.721 --> 00:39:50.140
(screams echoing)

555
00:39:55.854 --> 00:39:58.815
(screaming subsides)

556
00:39:59.733 --> 00:40:02.027
(indistinct chatter)

557
00:40:10.702 --> 00:40:11.870
Daemon: Up.

558
00:40:12.370 --> 00:40:14.160
Alys Rivers: You were
born to wield a sword.

559
00:40:14.164 --> 00:40:18.331
but not so much an axe. perhaps.

560
00:40:18.335 --> 00:40:20.041
Daemon: There are others
who would sit idle

561
00:40:20.045 --> 00:40:22.209
and wait for their claims
to be brought to them.

562
00:40:22.213 --> 00:40:25.671
- That is not my way.
- Does splitting firewood justify what's followed you here?

563
00:40:25.675 --> 00:40:27.715
Let it not be said
that Daemon Targaryen

564
00:40:27.719 --> 00:40:30.009
failed to dirty his
hands in this war.

565
00:40:30.013 --> 00:40:32.182
Oh. let me see them.

566
00:40:33.058 --> 00:40:35.101
- Sit.
- Daemon: Ah.

567
00:40:35.227 --> 00:40:36.394
Sit!

568
00:40:39.898 --> 00:40:43.189
(sighs) I hear strange
things from Bracken land.

569
00:40:43.193 --> 00:40:46.571
from Stone Hedge and
Lambswold and Mory.

570
00:40:47.572 --> 00:40:49.570
There's news. then?

571
00:40:49.574 --> 00:40:50.951
News?

572
00:40:52.118 --> 00:40:53.119
No.

573
00:40:55.080 --> 00:40:57.870
What I hear. I hear in the wind.

574
00:40:57.874 --> 00:41:01.086
- (screams echoing)
- Cries of anguish.

575
00:41:02.921 --> 00:41:04.919
Children being taken
from their mothers.

576
00:41:04.923 --> 00:41:08.881
men coming home to find
their doors unlatched...

577
00:41:08.885 --> 00:41:11.259
their wives carried away.

578
00:41:11.263 --> 00:41:13.386
(screaming subsides)

579
00:41:13.390 --> 00:41:16.142
War is a terrible thing.

580
00:41:16.268 --> 00:41:18.103
This is not war.

581
00:41:18.770 --> 00:41:21.227
These are crimes
against the innocent.

582
00:41:21.231 --> 00:41:23.396
that any upright
man would repudiate.

583
00:41:23.400 --> 00:41:26.232
Surely you haven't mistaken
me for an upright man.

584
00:41:26.236 --> 00:41:28.067
(Alys chuckles)

585
00:41:28.071 --> 00:41:31.612
The Brackens had their
chance to do as I required.

586
00:41:31.616 --> 00:41:33.906
They will perhaps think
better of their decision

587
00:41:33.910 --> 00:41:37.289
if their children's
lives are staked on it.

588
00:41:38.331 --> 00:41:41.126
Is that the kind of
army you would raise?

589
00:41:41.918 --> 00:41:44.129
Men who hate you...

590
00:41:44.629 --> 00:41:46.252
who serve you under duress?

591
00:41:46.256 --> 00:41:49.467
Well. once they agree to serve
me. I'll treat them fairly.

592
00:41:49.593 --> 00:41:50.756
Set an example for the rest

593
00:41:50.760 --> 00:41:52.804
of the Riverlands to follow.

594
00:41:52.929 --> 00:41:55.181
And once again. in
the name of power.

595
00:41:55.307 --> 00:41:58.310
it's the weak and the
women who must endure.

596
00:42:00.979 --> 00:42:04.024
That fool. Aegon. is
unlike to survive.

597
00:42:05.984 --> 00:42:08.361
The realm will suffer
if Aemond One-Eye rules.

598
00:42:09.821 --> 00:42:11.489
You should pray
you never meet him.

599
00:42:11.990 --> 00:42:14.159
He will cut you down soon
as wish you good-day.

600
00:42:14.284 --> 00:42:15.827
I'd heard the same
thing about you.

601
00:42:15.952 --> 00:42:16.949
But I'll cross you no further.

602
00:42:16.953 --> 00:42:18.496
I'm sure your tactics
are. after all.

603
00:42:18.622 --> 00:42:20.453
approved by the queen.

604
00:42:20.457 --> 00:42:23.501
(tense music playing)

605
00:42:25.879 --> 00:42:28.298
She cannot succeed. Alys.

606
00:42:28.840 --> 00:42:30.963
Even if I willed it to be so.

607
00:42:30.967 --> 00:42:33.011
The people who support her
will not be led by her.

608
00:42:33.136 --> 00:42:35.134
They look to a man for strength.

609
00:42:35.138 --> 00:42:36.223
Who's better suited to it?

610
00:42:36.348 --> 00:42:38.804
The Hightowers with
their scheming?

611
00:42:38.808 --> 00:42:41.228
Or Viserys's first true heir?

612
00:42:42.187 --> 00:42:44.685
When I take King's Landing...

613
00:42:44.689 --> 00:42:46.145
Rhaenyra is welcome
to join me there

614
00:42:46.149 --> 00:42:48.693
and take her place by my side.

615
00:42:48.818 --> 00:42:52.822
King and queen...
ruling together.

616
00:42:53.323 --> 00:42:56.030
- And if you lose?
- Then I'll be dead.

617
00:42:56.034 --> 00:42:58.324
and none of this
will be my problem.

618
00:42:58.328 --> 00:43:01.706
It's a pity. don't you think.
that you never knew your mother?

619
00:43:01.831 --> 00:43:04.042
♪

620
00:43:05.210 --> 00:43:07.545
Simon: A message. Your Grace.

621
00:43:09.339 --> 00:43:10.340
Uh...

622
00:43:12.425 --> 00:43:15.262
uh. fresh news from Stone Hedge.

623
00:43:15.387 --> 00:43:17.510
The Blackwoods have
overwhelmed the Brackens.

624
00:43:17.514 --> 00:43:21.226
and. uh. Lord Amos has
pledged his banner to you.

625
00:43:21.560 --> 00:43:23.728
House Bracken is yours.

626
00:43:24.896 --> 00:43:27.857
Call Ser Willem here so that
I might congratulate him.

627
00:43:28.191 --> 00:43:31.069
The Blackwoods will be
feted in these halls.

628
00:43:31.945 --> 00:43:35.198
- (bird cawing)
- (dog barking)

629
00:43:37.742 --> 00:43:39.953
(waves crashing)

630
00:43:42.247 --> 00:43:44.416
I sought you at High Tide.

631
00:43:45.041 --> 00:43:47.419
I was surprised when
they said you were here.

632
00:43:48.587 --> 00:43:50.589
My castle is a tomb.

633
00:43:51.798 --> 00:43:53.967
Empty. Haunted.

634
00:43:54.634 --> 00:43:57.971
I am sad to have missed
its highest days.

635
00:43:58.763 --> 00:44:00.052
I imagine your Hall of Nine

636
00:44:00.056 --> 00:44:02.388
filled with lords and kings.

637
00:44:02.392 --> 00:44:05.645
all eager to treat with the
legendary Lord of the Tides.

638
00:44:07.397 --> 00:44:08.561
The wealth you brought back

639
00:44:08.565 --> 00:44:09.896
from Yi Ti and Asshai.

640
00:44:09.900 --> 00:44:13.278
inspiring awe and envy.

641
00:44:15.447 --> 00:44:17.657
I wonder if any of them
knew it was all for her.

642
00:44:26.625 --> 00:44:29.002
Queen Rhaenyra wishes
to name you Hand.

643
00:44:29.127 --> 00:44:30.962
(Corlys sighs)

644
00:44:32.339 --> 00:44:36.468
Even the death of my wife
does not content her.

645
00:44:38.470 --> 00:44:40.847
Has she not asked
enough of my house?

646
00:44:41.306 --> 00:44:44.142
It is a sign of
her great esteem.

647
00:44:45.101 --> 00:44:47.021
Or does she think the
position will compensate me

648
00:44:47.145 --> 00:44:49.435
for my loss?

649
00:44:49.439 --> 00:44:51.938
Pledge your peace to
King's Landing. then.

650
00:44:51.942 --> 00:44:54.361
They will accept
it most gleefully.

651
00:44:56.655 --> 00:44:59.616
Rather I would sail into
the West and be lost.

652
00:45:00.700 --> 00:45:02.494
You have done so before.

653
00:45:02.619 --> 00:45:05.538
at great cost to yourself
and those who loved you.

654
00:45:07.999 --> 00:45:11.211
Rhaenys was not
only your wife...

655
00:45:11.336 --> 00:45:13.797
not a thing to be
taken from you.

656
00:45:14.464 --> 00:45:17.842
She was a Targaryen princess.

657
00:45:17.968 --> 00:45:19.173
The Queen Who Never Was.

658
00:45:19.177 --> 00:45:21.968
And she flew to Rook's
Rest of her own will.

659
00:45:21.972 --> 00:45:24.303
- In defense of her kin.
- And she died.

660
00:45:24.307 --> 00:45:26.643
She died as she would
have wished to die...

661
00:45:27.185 --> 00:45:30.355
with honor. in dragon fire.

662
00:45:30.855 --> 00:45:32.315
The way my mother chose...

663
00:45:34.359 --> 00:45:37.362
and the way I myself
wish to meet my end.

664
00:45:41.324 --> 00:45:44.244
(solemn music playing)

665
00:45:44.369 --> 00:45:47.660
I grieve my grandmother
who loved me

666
00:45:47.664 --> 00:45:49.874
but I carry her on with me.

667
00:45:50.917 --> 00:45:55.547
I will see Rhaenyra ascend the
Iron Throne. as Rhaenys wished.

668
00:45:56.047 --> 00:45:58.216
As Rhaenys herself should have.

669
00:46:00.677 --> 00:46:03.555
You yourself may
do as you see fit.

670
00:46:07.058 --> 00:46:08.681
Granddaughter.

671
00:46:08.685 --> 00:46:10.729
♪

672
00:46:16.067 --> 00:46:19.404
I would make you my heir.

673
00:46:20.864 --> 00:46:22.866
I am blood and fire.

674
00:46:23.283 --> 00:46:26.536
Driftmark must pass
to salt and sea.

675
00:46:34.920 --> 00:46:37.255
(music fades out)

676
00:46:45.096 --> 00:46:46.473
Your Grace.

677
00:46:50.060 --> 00:46:51.478
You were correct...

678
00:46:52.771 --> 00:46:55.732
in saying our best hope
of an army is with Daemon.

679
00:46:58.068 --> 00:47:03.782
And I have. perhaps. erred in
waiting for him to prove himself.

680
00:47:05.784 --> 00:47:07.786
I wish you to go to Harrenhal.

681
00:47:09.454 --> 00:47:12.123
Are you removing me
from your council?

682
00:47:13.625 --> 00:47:14.960
Ser Alfred...

683
00:47:15.669 --> 00:47:19.293
I-I-I will not deny you have
tried my patience of late.

684
00:47:19.297 --> 00:47:21.466
or that I would prefer a council

685
00:47:21.591 --> 00:47:23.134
more inclined to
champion their queen.

686
00:47:23.260 --> 00:47:25.925
but... (inhales)

687
00:47:25.929 --> 00:47:29.262
you and your house
served my father well.

688
00:47:29.266 --> 00:47:32.519
and I know you will never
accept the Hightower claim.

689
00:47:34.020 --> 00:47:36.773
Not while I live. Your Grace.

690
00:47:39.442 --> 00:47:43.109
We cannot challenge King's
Landing without the Riverlands

691
00:47:43.113 --> 00:47:47.284
but I will not send a message by
raven for Daemon to disregard.

692
00:47:49.327 --> 00:47:55.375
I ask you to...
reason with him.

693
00:47:55.500 --> 00:48:00.338
Find out his state of
mind and his intentions.

694
00:48:02.048 --> 00:48:03.633
Intentions?

695
00:48:04.509 --> 00:48:08.305
Whether he means to raise a
host for me or for himself.

696
00:48:11.141 --> 00:48:12.350
He would not dare.

697
00:48:12.475 --> 00:48:15.353
(scoffs) Have you known
Daemon to lack in daring?

698
00:48:16.855 --> 00:48:18.398
Go now with haste.

699
00:48:18.523 --> 00:48:21.359
I'll send good men to
see to your safety.

700
00:48:28.867 --> 00:48:31.536
Have you any message for him?

701
00:48:35.165 --> 00:48:38.710
Tell him I would much like to
finish our last conversation.

702
00:48:41.087 --> 00:48:42.505
Your Grace.

703
00:48:49.721 --> 00:48:52.682
- (rumbling)
- (water dripping)

704
00:48:53.892 --> 00:48:55.894
(eerie warbling)

705
00:49:03.902 --> 00:49:05.612
(footsteps approach)

706
00:49:13.787 --> 00:49:15.789
(knocking on door)

707
00:49:18.583 --> 00:49:20.293
Simon: Your Grace.

708
00:49:21.795 --> 00:49:23.296
(panting)

709
00:49:23.755 --> 00:49:28.093
What is it. Ser Simon? Is
the pudding now served?

710
00:49:28.635 --> 00:49:31.137
The Riverlords have
come. Your Grace.

711
00:49:31.263 --> 00:49:34.099
- They wish an audience.
- Now?

712
00:49:34.599 --> 00:49:37.102
- What godless hour is it?
- The wolf.

713
00:49:37.727 --> 00:49:39.771
They are demanding
to speak presently.

714
00:49:42.107 --> 00:49:45.277
(tense music playing)

715
00:49:58.415 --> 00:50:00.625
♪

716
00:50:10.635 --> 00:50:14.014
I see I must begin here
with a lesson in etiquette.

717
00:50:14.139 --> 00:50:15.261
Or failing that. in proper fear

718
00:50:15.265 --> 00:50:17.475
of your Targaryen master.

719
00:50:18.977 --> 00:50:23.481
Is there some reason you feel
free to wake a king in his bed?

720
00:50:24.190 --> 00:50:26.772
Or shall I now begin
your education?

721
00:50:26.776 --> 00:50:28.107
House Bracken

722
00:50:28.111 --> 00:50:31.865
have been brought to heel at
the hands of Willem Blackwood.

723
00:50:31.990 --> 00:50:35.323
- That news is stale.
- (chuckles) Yes.

724
00:50:35.327 --> 00:50:37.283
There have been.
um. complications.

725
00:50:37.287 --> 00:50:39.785
The sacred septs
on Bracken lands

726
00:50:39.789 --> 00:50:43.209
- were looted and burned.
- As were the fields and farms.

727
00:50:43.335 --> 00:50:44.669
The livestock was stolen

728
00:50:44.794 --> 00:50:46.334
and our peasants
put to the sword.

729
00:50:46.338 --> 00:50:49.007
They pursued the women
and the children.

730
00:50:49.132 --> 00:50:50.463
There were works of barbarity.

731
00:50:50.467 --> 00:50:54.221
Punishing Bracken for his own
treasons is one thing. aye.

732
00:50:54.346 --> 00:50:57.015
- But these other acts.
- The Brackens were given their chance.

733
00:50:57.140 --> 00:50:59.639
- They would not see reason.
- The Blackwoods have exploited

734
00:50:59.643 --> 00:51:01.474
the war for the crown
to visit atrocities

735
00:51:01.478 --> 00:51:04.018
- upon their old rivals.
- Piper: I have seen my fair share of their quarrels.

736
00:51:04.022 --> 00:51:05.686
and I tell you. there
is no honor in a fight

737
00:51:05.690 --> 00:51:07.647
- such as this.
- Honor? What of common decency?

738
00:51:07.651 --> 00:51:10.028
These beasts proudly carried

739
00:51:10.153 --> 00:51:11.905
the banner of House Targaryen.

740
00:51:12.030 --> 00:51:13.865
Red dragon on black.

741
00:51:16.368 --> 00:51:18.536
(eerie warbling)

742
00:51:20.205 --> 00:51:23.708
female voice: A terrible war
is being fought in these lands.

743
00:51:26.920 --> 00:51:29.172
Have you looked after our girls?

744
00:51:31.383 --> 00:51:34.553
(ominous music playing)

745
00:51:36.555 --> 00:51:38.595
Darry: We should've expected
nothing more from a man

746
00:51:38.682 --> 00:51:40.600
who ordered the
slaughter of a child

747
00:51:40.725 --> 00:51:42.435
in his mother's arms.

748
00:51:44.229 --> 00:51:47.607
That is a lie. And I will have the
man who told it brought before me.

749
00:51:47.732 --> 00:51:52.571
Well. your man is half
the kingdom. my prince.

750
00:51:55.407 --> 00:51:57.409
Know this. interloper:

751
00:51:57.909 --> 00:52:00.745
the Riverlands are
an ancient place.

752
00:52:00.870 --> 00:52:04.583
watched closely by the
eyes of old gods and new.

753
00:52:04.958 --> 00:52:06.626
And dragon or no.

754
00:52:06.751 --> 00:52:10.088
we shall not raise our
banners for a tyrant.

755
00:52:13.258 --> 00:52:16.469
(tense music playing)

756
00:52:27.939 --> 00:52:29.941
♪

757
00:52:52.088 --> 00:52:54.090
(indistinct chatter)

758
00:52:55.967 --> 00:52:57.969
♪

759
00:53:15.987 --> 00:53:17.822
♪

760
00:53:17.948 --> 00:53:21.993
- Move along. lass.
- I have an errand... for the lady Mysaria.

761
00:53:23.161 --> 00:53:24.329
I thought she was dead.

762
00:53:25.121 --> 00:53:27.666
Would she die without
collecting her due?

763
00:53:29.167 --> 00:53:31.044
I must see an old friend.

764
00:53:32.671 --> 00:53:34.839
Most people want out these days.

765
00:53:38.134 --> 00:53:40.136
♪

766
00:53:48.186 --> 00:53:50.188
♪

767
00:53:57.237 --> 00:53:58.989
(rain pattering)

768
00:54:04.035 --> 00:54:07.038
- (indistinct chatter)
- (thunder rumbling)

769
00:54:16.715 --> 00:54:18.925
(music softens)

770
00:54:20.093 --> 00:54:21.052
Elinda.

771
00:54:21.177 --> 00:54:23.096
(wind blowing)

772
00:54:23.221 --> 00:54:26.224
(pensive music playing)

773
00:54:28.393 --> 00:54:30.562
(deep breathing)

774
00:54:45.744 --> 00:54:47.366
(thunder rumbling)

775
00:54:47.370 --> 00:54:50.624
(tense music playing)

776
00:54:52.375 --> 00:54:55.086
(unsettling vocalizing)

777
00:55:05.263 --> 00:55:07.265
♪

778
00:55:12.771 --> 00:55:14.981
Was it worth the price?

779
00:55:21.446 --> 00:55:23.657
(shallow breathing)

780
00:55:27.452 --> 00:55:29.120
(thunder continues)

781
00:55:29.246 --> 00:55:32.249
(solemn music playing)

782
00:55:55.480 --> 00:55:57.482
♪

783
00:56:02.654 --> 00:56:04.864
(door opens)

784
00:56:05.824 --> 00:56:07.784
(hoarsely) Mummy.

785
00:56:10.996 --> 00:56:12.998
♪

786
00:56:18.336 --> 00:56:19.792
(footstep approach)

787
00:56:19.796 --> 00:56:22.173
(music fades out)

788
00:56:24.676 --> 00:56:26.219
Prince Jacaerys. Your Grace.

789
00:56:43.653 --> 00:56:46.031
(distant dragon grumbles)

790
00:56:51.036 --> 00:56:52.370
Visenya.

791
00:56:53.204 --> 00:56:58.919
Vhagar's first rider. and the
first wielder of Dark Sister.

792
00:57:00.378 --> 00:57:02.835
I hope you do not mean
to use her as an example.

793
00:57:02.839 --> 00:57:04.545
Why shouldn't I?

794
00:57:04.549 --> 00:57:06.927
W... It was a long time ago.

795
00:57:17.020 --> 00:57:19.397
What is the mood at the Twins?

796
00:57:20.899 --> 00:57:23.235
Did his lordship quibble?

797
00:57:25.403 --> 00:57:29.366
He wishes for the Freys
to be granted Harrenhal.

798
00:57:30.742 --> 00:57:33.078
At war's end. Assuming.

799
00:57:35.747 --> 00:57:37.290
I'm proud of you. Jace.

800
00:57:37.415 --> 00:57:39.918
You have done our
cause a great service.

801
00:57:42.128 --> 00:57:45.131
Then. why do you look angry?

802
00:57:51.763 --> 00:57:53.219
(sighs)

803
00:57:53.223 --> 00:57:56.222
You chafed at being
prevented from action.

804
00:57:56.226 --> 00:57:59.058
Imagine my lot. I'm a
dragon rider as well.

805
00:57:59.062 --> 00:58:02.107
with a war being fought
over my ascension.

806
00:58:03.108 --> 00:58:05.277
And yet. I must wait here...

807
00:58:06.278 --> 00:58:08.568
always prudent...

808
00:58:08.572 --> 00:58:09.944
sending others to fight

809
00:58:09.948 --> 00:58:12.409
and be felled in my name.

810
00:58:12.784 --> 00:58:15.161
Even you have managed
to do your part.

811
00:58:15.745 --> 00:58:17.455
Jacaerys Velaryon:
You are the queen...

812
00:58:17.831 --> 00:58:19.078
the tie that binds us.

813
00:58:19.082 --> 00:58:20.913
- No harm can come to you.
- And you are my son.

814
00:58:20.917 --> 00:58:23.128
and I did not give
you leave to go.

815
00:58:24.963 --> 00:58:27.674
You do not give me
leave to go to anything.

816
00:58:28.008 --> 00:58:29.255
But who else is there?
Rhaenys is dead.

817
00:58:29.259 --> 00:58:31.132
and Baela cannot bear
the burden alone.

818
00:58:31.136 --> 00:58:33.801
And when Aemond comes
hunting for you?

819
00:58:33.805 --> 00:58:36.137
Your dragon is young.

820
00:58:36.141 --> 00:58:38.435
Will you fly before
Vhagar as Luke did?

821
00:58:45.150 --> 00:58:47.277
Perhaps Daemon could...

822
00:58:50.655 --> 00:58:52.490
Daemon is not here.

823
00:58:53.199 --> 00:58:56.782
And Aemond now rules
in King's Landing.

824
00:58:56.786 --> 00:59:01.120
- Is Aegon dead?
- Dead or alive. we have no answer for Vhagar.

825
00:59:01.124 --> 00:59:04.502
Aemond will not wait long to press
his advantage. And then what?

826
00:59:06.963 --> 00:59:08.673
I have done all I can from here.

827
00:59:08.798 --> 00:59:11.505
sent my messages.
invoked my alliances.

828
00:59:11.509 --> 00:59:14.137
But if all else fails.
it is I who must fight.

829
00:59:15.847 --> 00:59:18.638
Vhagar is big. but
Syrax is quicker.

830
00:59:18.642 --> 00:59:23.396
- So was Meleys.
- Meleys fought two dragons and one of them is slain.

831
00:59:24.981 --> 00:59:26.261
Shall I fight for my birthright?

832
00:59:26.316 --> 00:59:29.194
Or shall I wait here until
we are all destroyed?

833
00:59:34.866 --> 00:59:37.035
I need dragons.

834
00:59:40.205 --> 00:59:43.375
We have no dearth of dragons.

835
00:59:44.042 --> 00:59:47.041
We have two large enough
to stand against Vhagar.

836
00:59:47.045 --> 00:59:50.336
They are called
Vermithor and Silverwing

837
00:59:50.340 --> 00:59:51.883
and they sleep just
beneath our feet.

838
00:59:52.008 --> 00:59:53.089
Yes. and if only
they had riders.

839
00:59:53.093 --> 00:59:55.387
none could stand against me.

840
00:59:56.012 --> 00:59:59.391
I would go forth in strength
and not from necessity.

841
01:00:00.684 --> 01:00:01.935
There is Rhaena.

842
01:00:02.060 --> 01:00:05.230
(scoffs) Who nearly lost her
life in her last attempt.

843
01:00:06.606 --> 01:00:08.608
I would not risk it again.

844
01:00:14.406 --> 01:00:17.576
There are those of our
line who never ruled.

845
01:00:18.243 --> 01:00:21.788
Those who married into
other noble houses.

846
01:00:21.913 --> 01:00:24.537
their children born
with other names.

847
01:00:24.541 --> 01:00:28.374
A generation ago. or more.
Their blood would be thin.

848
01:00:28.378 --> 01:00:29.754
And yet...

849
01:00:30.880 --> 01:00:35.214
A dragon will only accept a
dragon lord to ride it. (Sighs)

850
01:00:35.218 --> 01:00:39.218
- Or so say the histories.
- (chuckles) Valyrian histories.

851
01:00:39.222 --> 01:00:41.387
Written to gild us in glory.

852
01:00:41.391 --> 01:00:44.098
(chuckles)

853
01:00:44.102 --> 01:00:46.897
Are you suggesting we put
a Mallister on a dragon?

854
01:00:47.314 --> 01:00:51.109
- A Tarly?
- It's better than death and defeat.

855
01:00:56.907 --> 01:01:00.239
There are records here.
surely. of our line

856
01:01:00.243 --> 01:01:02.621
and of those who fell out of it.

857
01:01:02.746 --> 01:01:05.749
(intense music playing)

858
01:01:10.086 --> 01:01:11.751
There could be scores of them.

859
01:01:11.755 --> 01:01:13.340
(exhales)

860
01:01:19.471 --> 01:01:21.348
It's a mad thought.

861
01:01:24.100 --> 01:01:26.311
♪

862
01:01:30.649 --> 01:01:33.026
(music fades out)

863
01:01:37.614 --> 01:01:40.617
♪

864
01:02:08.019 --> 01:02:10.188
♪

865
01:02:45.223 --> 01:02:47.601
(music fades out)

866
01:02:53.356 --> 01:02:54.276
♪ (PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYS)

867
01:02:55.305 --> 01:03:55.357
